<br>
The Cancel Magic line (Dispell magic, Annul Magic etc.) remove buffs or debuffs spell effects that are on the target.  You can buff you pet (burnout or damage shield) and then cancel magic on it to see its effect (&amp; amount of success).<br>
<br>
Think of it as an &quot;unbuff&quot; for now.  Caster mobs will buff themselves, and sometimes their friends (watch them after they pop).  If you &quot;unbuff&quot; them with cancel magic, you'll get two benefits:  (1) You'll pull the target to you (at a safer location) with a very mild amount of hate -- the first hit from your pet will make it hate the pet more than you.  (2) The target may lose a buff and be easier to kill.<br>
<br>
BTW, you should be using /pet report health (as a hotkey) -- you'll see the pet buffs / debuffs, and the health report can be more accurate than the life bar when your pet is away from you, so you may have fewer surprise pet deaths.<br>
